Chapter 12: The Great Escape
The Library’s stained-glass windows shattered inward as a dozen flash-bang grenades arced through the air. Ren didn’t wait for the light. He dove behind a fallen bookshelf, shielding his eyes as the room erupted in a blinding, white-hot glare.
[Status: Sensory Overload (Suppressed)]
[Action: Spend 10 Stat Points?]
All into Agility and Processing, Ren thought. He felt his nerves catch fire—not with heat, but with speed. The world slowed down. The falling dust motes hung in the air like diamonds.
[Processing Speed: +200%]
[New Passive: 'Overclocked Reflexes' Active.]
"Target is near the west wing lockers!" a voice echoed.
Ren didn't run for the door. He ran for the high, shattered window. As he sprinted, a Null-Field—a shimmering blue net of energy designed to suppress Essence—dropped from the ceiling.
"The Null-Field won't work on him!" Vane’s voice screamed over the comms. "He’s not using Essence! Physical restraint only!"
Ren leapt.
A heavy, mechanical claw—a capture drone—shot out from the shadows, snapping toward his ankle. In mid-air, Ren didn't even look back. He twisted his body, his fingers grazing the 'Project Architect' folder in his jacket.
[Skill Trigger: Structural Deconstruction (Partial)]
[Target: Capture Drone 01]
He touched the drone's metal casing for a fraction of a second.
Cling.
The drone didn't break; it simply forgot how to fly. Its gravity-repulsors flickered out, and it slammed into the floor like a lead weight. Ren caught the edge of the window frame and pulled himself out onto the narrow stone ledge three stories above the Academy courtyard.
Below, the campus was a sea of red searchlights. Hundreds of students were being herded into the dorms, while black-clad Enforcers flooded the grounds.
"There he is!"
A hail of rubber-coated kinetic slugs whistled past his head, chipping the stonework.
"Ren!"
He looked down. In the shadows of the courtyard's fountain, a figure was waving frantically. It was Mira. She was holding her Resonance Staff, but it was glowing with the silver light Ren had gifted it in the Breach.
"This way! The drainage tunnels!" she shouted, her voice barely a whisper through the chaos.
Ren looked at the ledge, then at the Enforcers rappelling down from the roof above him. He had no choice. He let go.
The wind whipped past his ears. Just before he hit the ground, Mira slammed her staff into the pavement. A localized sound-wave cushioned his fall, turning the impact into a soft thud.
"Mira? Why are you helping me?" Ren gasped, pushing himself up. "They’ll label you an Anomaly too."
"They already are," Mira said, her eyes wide with fear but her hands steady. "Jax is gone, Ren. The Association took him to a 'rehabilitation center' an hour ago. And I saw what they did to Kaelen. That wasn't an upgrade. It was a lobotomy."
She grabbed his hand. "The tunnels lead to the old city ruins. The Association’s scanners can't penetrate the deep-level Void-rot there. If we make it to the perimeter, we can disappear."
"I can't let you do this," Ren said.
"Too late," she replied, pointing behind them.
Warden Vane was standing on the library balcony, looking down at them. He wasn't yelling anymore. He was holding a sleek, silver remote.
"Ren!" Vane’s voice boomed across the courtyard, amplified by the Academy’s speakers. "You think you're escaping? You're just moving to a larger cage. I’m activating the Academy's Perimeter Shield. Nothing—not even a bug—leaves this campus."
A massive dome of golden energy began to shimmer into existence at the edges of the school grounds. It wasn't a Veil; it was a cage.
[Warning: Global System Lockdown in Progress.]
[The Administrator has logged in.]
"Mira, the staff," Ren said, his eyes turning silver. "I need to 'Redirect' the sound-wave. We aren't going under the wall. We're going through it."
"But the shield is S-Rank!"
"The shield is just a piece of code," Ren said, his hand beginning to glitch with static. "And I just found the Backdoor."
The escape is on. Ren and Mira are headed for the edge of the world they once knew.
